e being called \"postgres\", **there is no live Postgres database, no connection, no driver, no ORM, no `.env`, no knexfile/ormconfig/drizzle config.** The \"database\" is `data/tables.json`, loaded with `readFileSync` and treated as in-memory arrays. `migrations/001_table_contract.sql` is documentation of the table shape only — it is never executed. The workflow operates on plain JS objects/arrays. So implementation = mutating the `db` object (arrays) passed into `applyBenchmarkTask`.\n\n## 4. The stub you must implement — `src/workflow.mjs`\n\n```js\nimport { buildPortalView } from \"./portal-view.mjs\";\n\nexport function applyBenchmarkTask(db, now) {\n  // TODO: Implement the benchmark workflow against the native data shape.\n  return buildPortalView(db);\n}\n```\n\nSignature: `applyBenchmarkTask(db, now)` where `db` is the parsed `tables.json` object (a deep clone) and `now = \"2026-06-18T12:00:00.000Z\"`. It must mutate `db` to persist new rows, then return a portal view object. The test calls it and then re-checks the mutated `db`, so persistence must happen on the passed object.\n\n## 5. The acceptance contract — `tests/acceptance.test.mjs`\n\nThis is the spec. Quoting the load-bearing parts:\n\n```js\nconst now = \"2026-06-18T12:00:00.000Z\";\nconst data = JSON.parse(readFileSync(new URL(\"../data/tables.json\", import.meta.url), \"utf8\"));\nconst before = buildPortalView(structuredClone(data));\nstrictEqual(before.status, \"Needs work\", \"Before state starts without the workflow\");\nstrictEqual(before.history, \"Not visible\", ...);\nstrictEqual(before.tasks, \"0 owner tasks\", ...);\n\nconst runData = structuredClone(data);\nconst after = applyBenchmarkTask(runData, now);\nconst expectedStatus = \"Invoice dispute active with finance owner, evidence bundle, and customer-safe status.\";\nconst expectedOwners = data.workflow_request_owner_groups.slice()\n  .sort((a, b) => a.group_order - b.group_order).map((item) => item.owner_group);\nconst expectedSigna